Assess what parts of the capabilities matrix can be enforced using available Unix/container mechanisms under the actual constraints (single uid/gid, no sudo, no setuid/setgid helpers, “no new privileges”, but remounting may be possible via remountd). The outcome is a clear statement of what can be made watertight (e.g. mount-level RO/RW), what cannot (e.g. chmod-based restrictions against the same uid), and what failure modes/messages are needed to keep agents from “working around” intentional restrictions.
